{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1597408615,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU2NzkxMjg3MDM=","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/134","origin":"github"},"title":"One more PRVHASH variant: prvhash82","message":"I've just released prvhash82 function - it is the same algorithm, but extended to 128-bit math, produces hashes in 64-bit length increments. It's twice as fast as prvhash42, the only drawback is it's not very portable and not very good for short messages (bad biases for 16-bit sparse and combinations). Otherwise it shows exponentially better bit biases in most tests. Maybe you could add prvhash82_64 and prvhash82_128 tests? https://github.com/avaneev/prvhash","files":null}]}